description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and innovative Qualified Nurse (RGN) with a passionate for excellent delivery of high quality care within our Continence Service her in Trafford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Band 6 Registered Nurse to work in the Adult Bladder and Bowel Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have an interest in Bladder and Bowel dysfunction and working in various care settings including clinics, patients&#39; own homes and residential homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for providing holistic bladder and bowel assessments, participating in treatment planning and evaluating individual continence needs. The successful candidate will also assist in training and supporting Community Nurses in delivering educational programmes for healthcare professionals, carers and patients being fully supported to develop skills and knowledge to practice in the specialist area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Bladder and Bowel service is dynamic and forward-thinking, anticipating the needs of its patients and striving to provide excellence care in the community. We are also highly active in engaging with community staff to improve services within TLCO.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will possess excellent interpersonal and communication skills that will demonstrate an ability to liaise with internal and external stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be car driver with the use of a car for work and a prescribing qualification is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For more information about the post please call:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
